{
  "text": "where \u03bb = (\u03bb 1 , \u03bb 2 , . . .) and f \u03bb denotes the number of SYT of shape \u03bb as in Section 3. Equation (5) is due to Craige Schensted [CITATION_1] and is an immediate consequence of the Robinson-Schensted-Knuth algorithm; see also [37, Exer. 7 .109(a)].",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "121435038"
